        Official Singles Chart on 21/8/2020

        21 August 2020 - 27 August 2020

        The Official UK Singles Chart reflects the UK’s biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1 and MTV, the Top 100 is published exclusively on OfficialCharts.com. View the biggest songs of 2024 so far.

        Hey Jeremy! :)

        Sorry about that! I guess I was so busy that I just forgot, haha.

        This was the top Reddit comment on the differences between the two forms of rap, which I also thought was a very good way of separating grime & drill...

        "Difference tends to be the BPM (for the most part it seems drills catching up) in the beats and also the general theme of it. Grime tracks tend to be fast paced and quite punchy with the sounds where as Drill tends to be a lot slower and relies on more melodies. Hi hats tend to be used more in grime too.

        Other than that the flows tend to be completely different with grime having a much faster pattern. Lyrics can be similar but drill tends to be more violent and actually targeted at someone/somewhere where as grime tends to be more in general."

        WEEKLY CHART REVIEW (21/08/2020 - 27/08/2020)

        🔴 (Negative)

        1) ‘Lighter’ dropped back to #3! I’m getting the sinking feeling that this won’t be going to be top of the charts after all.

        2) Jubel’s incredible cover of ‘Dancing In The Moonlight’ misses the Top 10… yet again!

        3) ‘Take You Dancing’ took a massive climb, which contains arguably Jason Derulo’s worst hook to date! It’s so annoying & creepy. Urgh!

        4) ‘Fake Friends’ seems to have lost its momentum!

        5) ‘Rain On Me’ took another massive fall this week! :’(

        🟠 (Mixed)

        1) ‘Wap’ climbed to the runner-up position to become Cardi B’s highest charting song in the UK to date. It’s grown on me a lot since last week, but not enough to put it in the “positive” section just yet.

        2) Drake unsurprisingly got the highest debut of the week, in the Top 5! In terms of production, this one stands out a lot, but the lyrics & delivery are just okay. I don’t know, this is better than most of his recent hits, but I don’t know how well it’s going to age for me!

        3) ‘Savage Love’ got hit by ACR harder than initially though this week, probably due to streaming starting to fade anyway.

        4) ‘Holiday’ moved up again! I’m slowly starting to get to this one now, although I hear it more on the radio rather than choosing to stream it myself.

        5) ‘Only You Freestyle’ dropped a fair bit, which is a shame as I’ve been playing that song a lot this past week!

        6) ‘Breaking Me’ fell a few places this week too! I actually like that song way more than most here do, haha.

        7) ‘Dance Monkey’ didn’t return to the Top 40, despite the midweek updates indicating it would.

        8) Taylor Swift lost the #1 album, but hey, she had a really good run there, so I’m still glad!

        🟢 (Positive)

        1) ‘Head & Heart’ stayed at #1 for a fifth week, which it also did on my personal chart! If the BuzzJack numbers are accurate enough, it should’ve got a 15k combined sales lead this week.

        2) While I don’t like TikTok at all, at least it’s pushing ‘Mood Swings’ higher up the chart!

        3) ‘Looking For Me’ was the joint highest climber this week, which could also be Top 10 next week!

        4) ‘Midnight Sky’ debuts in the Top 15! I really love that throwback disco sound for Miley, along with her unusually raw vocals. I hope she continues to make more music like this, because I’m loving this right now!

        5) ‘You Broke Me First’ made the Top 40! Thanks to Coolocelot for introducing this to me, haha. Many critics have named Tate McRae the Canadian Billie Eilish & I can definitely see why! This song is really dark & deep, but in a way that carries a lot of emotional weight.

        6) While I thought it would be higher, I love the remix of ‘Levitating’ making the Top 40! Hopefully it can be a slow burner & that it won’t be forgotten with the success of ‘Hallucinate’ (glad that one’s moving up though!). I still prefer the original version of this one though, but this is still awesome!

        That's it for now! Take care guys. :)

        COOLOCELOT’S CHART REVIEW

        hey pals and gals, it’s coolocelot101. tonight i’m gonna give you a review, but before we get into the new entries, i’ll observe the moves around the top 40.

        as you can see, “head & heart” is number 1 for a fifth week, with 68k overall units - i still like it, but it’s falling on streams for me and i hope “lighter” can get to number 1 asap. “wap” is one joel corry’s tail, while acr strikes “savage love” but i hate that song with a pure passion so i’m buzzing it’s dropping. “looking for me” swerves into the top 20, and i don’t mind that little move because it’s a decent dance song! also, "dance monkey" may be gone for good as it's dropped to number 42. ah well, let’s get into the top 40 entries.

        DRAKE FT LIL DURK - LAUGH NOW CRY LATER (#4)
        drake has been dominating the charts for years now, so it was no surprise that he scored the top debut lol. as for this, yeah it’s decent enough! i must say, i really like this beat with the blaring trumpets and booming bass over a clean trap beat, and i’ll always love drake’s crooning. if there’s anything to let this down for me, it’s lil durk’s delivery, he impressed me on “3 headed goat” but in this one he’s wailing a little. other than that, it’s another good song from drake! i’m gonna give this a light 7/10.

        MILEY CYRUS - MIDNIGHT SKY (#15)
        there was no way i wasn’t gonna cover this as miley has scored a lot of hits in the past few years! now we get to the song... oh, i love that echoing guitar line so much and the thumping beat comes in and already makes this an awesome indie-pop song! miley’s delivery is really anthemic in this track, and i really like that, especially when she belts out in that hook. not to mention the lyrics where she doesn’t need love and feels good on her own. overall, this is a song i could see myself having on repeat, and i hope it can get to number 1 someday. decent 8/10, good job miley!

        TATE MCRAE - YOU BROKE ME FIRST (#34)
        i found out about this song when it was lurking in the amazon music charts and on spotify playlists, and i’m absolutely buzzing that this hit the top 40, because i’ve really loved this one for a while now! i honestly think the downbeat, dramatic production suits a sad song like this. tate’s vocals may have had to grow on me, but i love the emotion she puts in this one! and then there’s the lyrics about tate’s past lover saying how bad it hurts that she left him, but he doesn’t feel as much pain as she does. look, as someone who battles loneliness, depression and sometimes suicidal thoughts on a regular basis, i could relate to this song a lot. so yeah, good job for giving tate mcrae a breakthrough hit, especially when the song is this good! strong 9/10.

        DUA LIPA FT MADONNA & MISSY ELLIOTT - LEVITATING (REMIX) (#39)
        i didn’t care for dua’s second album at all. i’m blessed that the better tracks from it (don’t start now, hallucinate and this) are singles. before i get into the remix, i have to talk about the original first: a funky disco song with lyrics about a love that feels like floating through space (strong 7/10 for that one). and i think the remix is even better! there was a change of production in this remix, but this one is more suited for clubs with the deep yet groovy keys and i like it even more than the original’s. so they added madonna and missy elliott to this and while i do think madonna does a fine enough job, missy’s rap in the middle really sealed the deal for me! 2020’s music scene has had some remixes to its name (say so, savage and don’t rush to name a few) but this one is just like those ones - a pleasure. light 8/10!

        on the albums chart, biffy clyro score their 3rd number 1 album with “a celebration of endings”! it debuted at number 1 with 26k chart sales.

        the rest of the top 5 is: “folklore” by taylor swift (1-2), “open your head” by sea girls (new at 3) “shoot for the stars, aim for the moon by pop smoke” (non-mover at 4) legends never die by juice wrld (non-mover at 5)

        looking ahead to next week, expect songs by the likes of clean bandit ft mabel & 24kgoldn, headie one ft aj tracey & stormzy, mariah carey ft lauryn hill, aitch, bts and maybe even more.

        that’s it i believe and wow! you know it was a very good week for the charts when drake got the worst of the week (even if the song is still good). i enjoyed putting this review together, and i hope you enjoyed reading. have a good weekend! :)
        P.S. my top 25 favourite songs of the week will come later tonight.
